my dad as your marketing guy.


229
0:9:45,31 --> 0:9:49,45
So he had all these, but
he couldn't sell them.


230
0:9:49,45 --> 0:9:50,82
But he decided on this.


231
0:9:50,82 --> 0:9:53,73
And he talked to this guy who
had all these service stations.


232
0:9:53,73 --> 0:9:58,83
And this guy decided
he'd look at it.


233
0:9:58,83 --> 0:10:2,81
And so my father set
up a demonstration.


234
0:10:2,81 --> 0:10:4,33
This was after my
mother had died.


235
0:10:4,33 --> 0:10:7,32
And my father had a
string of girlfriends.


236
0:10:7,32 --> 0:10:10,5
And the girlfriend
had this little dog.


237
0:10:10,5 --> 0:10:11,28
It was a mutt.


238
0:10:11,28 --> 0:10:12,51
But it was cute.


239
0:10:12,51 --> 0:10:15,1
And dog's name is Fluffy.


240
0:10:15,1 --> 0:10:17,14
And my father--
oh, I almost forgot


241
0:10:17,14 --> 0:10:19,59
one of the most
interesting things.


242
0:10:19,59 --> 0:10:21,6
My father had
pamphlets printed up.


243
0:10:21,6 --> 0:10:23,77
And the name was
also on the thing.


244
0:10:23,77 --> 0:10:26,19
And it was called
the Koontz Komfy Kot.


245
0:10:26,19 --> 0:10:27,88
And my father thought
it would be clever


246
0:10:27,88 --> 0:10:29,76
